<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2527</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-23T19:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 24, 1.15 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3658. Reichstag postponed discussion of the resolution on submarine
                                warfare in full session; the subject will be discussed in the Budget
                                Committee whose sessions commence next Monday. Cologne <hi rend="italic">Gazette</hi> quotes London <hi rend="italic">Times</hi> as reporting from Washington that the American
                                Government considers the British instructions to armed merchantmen
                                published by Germany sufficient proof that such vessels are armed
                                for defense only.</p>
                            <p>Semiofficially reported that reciprocity agreement has been concluded
                                by Germany with Roumania under which Germany and Austria receive
                                100,000 wagons of corn and 40,000 wagons of grain and malt.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>